# CIFAR-10 MLOps Pipeline

End-to-end MLOps pipeline for image classification using CIFAR-10 dataset, built as part of CMP5366.

## Architecture

A 3-block CNN trained on 60,000 CIFAR-10 images (32×32 RGB), served via FastAPI with real-time drift monitoring. All services run on a single AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance.

## Tech Stack

| Component | Tool | Purpose |
|-----------|------|---------|
| Database | PostgreSQL | Structured metadata (images, experiments, predictions) |
| Cache | Redis | Raw pixel array storage (key-value) |
| Orchestration | Apache Airflow | DAG-based pipeline automation |
| Experiment Tracking | MLflow | Parameters, metrics, model artifacts |
| API | FastAPI | Prediction serving + monitoring endpoints |
| Frontend | Streamlit | Dashboard with prediction, monitoring, drift tabs |
| Monitoring | Custom z-score + Evidently AI | Data drift detection |
| Containerisation | Docker Compose + Docker Hub | Service orchestration and image registry |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions | Automated linting and testing on push |

